  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering App Screens**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the initial framework for a web application called \"Highland Mist.\" I\'ve been reviewing the provided mockups and HTML documents. My goal is to structure the application\'s core elements based on these screen designs. I plan to determine the key components of the UI.\n\n\n**Defining App Features**\n\nI\'ve shifted my focus to the core features. \"Highland Mist\" is crystallizing as a cohesive travel and civic guide app for Baguio City. I\'ve broken down the design into tabbed screens. The \"Explore\" screen acts as a home base, \"Landmarks\" showcases iconic sites, and \"Culture\" highlights local traditions. \"Plan\" is next to guide users through trip planning.\n\n\n**Structuring App Screens**\n\nI\'m now structuring the single-page React application \"Highland Mist\" with seamless navigation between screens. I\'m focusing on \"Explore,\" \"Landmarks,\" \"Culture,\" \"Plan,\" \"Ordinances,\" and \"Education.\" I envision a fully custom, interactive design using React and Tailwind. I\'m now examining the file structure and `package.json` to verify the setup of the base application. I\'ve re-assessed the need for Firebase; persistent data isn\'t relevant for a guide. Standard client-side state is ideal for this informational application.\n\n\n**Adding AI Features**\n\nI\'m now investigating potential AI integration. Thinking about adding an interactive travel helper or search function using Gemini API. I think it would be a great value-add to the \"Explore\" or \"Plan\" tabs. I\'m also confirming the necessity and best location for any image generation features, as the HTML already hotlinks Google-hosted images.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 80033427
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
