    thinking: "**Reviewing Initial Success**\n\nI\'m incredibly pleased with the flawless build completion! My primary focus now shifts to rigorously validating all requirements. Specifically, I must confirm that the outcome strictly adheres to the user\'s explicit instructions, offering no deviation or extraneous elements. Ensuring this precise fulfillment is paramount.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have built and completed the screen designs and experiences for the **Highland Mist** application, establishing an authentic, high-contrast, alpine-themed guide to Baguio City. \n\nHere is a summary of the design pairings and final modules:\n\n- **Highland Spruce & Mist Palette**: Styled on a light theme with soft off-whites, misty-blue accents, and deep pine greens. We integrated elegant **Hanken Grotesk** display titles paired with clean **Inter** prose body and **JetBrains Mono** data tags to reinforce a Swiss-modern aesthetic.\n- **Translucent Top Navigation Header**: Custom sticky bar displaying a dynamic real-time clock synced to Baguio local standard time, a interactive global search bar, saved bookmarks folder trigger, and mobile drawer layout.\n- **Asymmetric Sights & Landmarks Grid**: Responsive bento cards for iconic locations like Burnham Park, Mines View, and Wright Park, incorporating entry details, opening hours, exact address overlays, and custom traveler tips.\n- **Live Culture & Celebrations Board**: Explains regional backstrap hand weaving, Asin Road silversmithing, Ifugao woodcarving cooperatives, and the annual floral parade floats of the Panagbenga Festival.\n- **Custom Escape Itinerary Builder**: An interactive planning simulator where users can input arrival travel season, duration, and pace focus to calculate personalized day-by-day itineraries and checklist recommendations.\n- **Civic Rules & Ordinances Directory**: Protects city heritage via clear guidelines on local laws (e.g., Smoke-Free City, Anti-Plastic, Night Sound levels). Included is an **Interactive Violation Dispatch Form** letting visitors submit simulated incidents directly to tourist police rangers.\n- **Higher Education Center Hub**: Provides comprehensive historic profiles for Baguio\'s universities and the iconic Thomasite heritage compound, Teachers Camp.\n- **Persistent Saved List**: A client-side state notebook backing up bookmarked destinations to let people check off visited locations, print travel summaries, or book pine-loggingHomestays.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 227429134
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
